<TITLE> Bangladesh avoid follow-on </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 17 (bdnews24.com) -- A seventh wicket turnaround after a characteristic top order collapse helped Bangladesh avoid following on against New Zealand in Hamilton on the third day of the only test. Shakib Al Hasan and Mahmudullah Riad came together when Bangladesh were reeling at 196 for 6, and added 145, chasing New Zealand's impressive 553 for 7 in the first innings. In the process Shakib, with 87, and Mahmudullah, with 115, not only took Bangladesh past the 400 mark but also broke the past seventh wicket stand for their team. Bangladesh ended with 408, and New Zealand were 9 losing one wicket at stumps on the third
